
<h1 align="center">CyberDojo</h1>
<h3 align="center">Practising the <em>collaborative</em> game called software development</h3>

<table valign="top" align="center">
<tr>
<td class="panel">
CyberDojo is a browser-based coding-<span title="a dojo is simply 'a place to practice'">dojo</span>
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;you write your code and tests in a simple editor inside a browser 
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;you click a button and the CyberDojo server runs your tests
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;that's it! nothing needs to be installed
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="panel">
  <form name="dojoNew" action="/dojo/new">
    First... 
    <div>choose a name
          <input type="text"
                 name="name"
                 value="" />
          and click
          <input type="submit"
                 id="new_button"
                 name="new"
                 value="Create our CyberDojo" />
          <% if flash[:new_notice] -%>
            <div class="notice"><%= flash[:new_notice] -%></div>
          <% end -%>
        </div>
      </form>
      
      <form name="dojoEnter" action="/dojo/enter">
      Then, at <em>each</em> computer...
        <div>type the name
          <input type="text"
                 name="name"
                 value="<%=@name-%>" />
          and click
          <input type="submit"
                 name="enter"
                 id="enter_button"
                 value="Enter our CyberDojo" />
          <% if flash[:enter_notice] -%>
            <div class="notice"><%= flash[:enter_notice] -%></div>
          <% end -%>
        </div>
      </form>
</td></tr>

<tr>
<td class="panel">
CyberDojo is designed to encourage <em>collaboration</em>
<br/>&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;gather some geek friends, split into groups, two or more people per group
<br/>&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;allocate one computer to each group, point each computer's browser here
<br/>&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;every 5 minutes you will be asked to rotate;
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;keyboard-drivers must then take up a non-driver role at a <em>different</em> computer
<br/>&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;the aim is to work <em>collectively</em> towards working solutions on <em>all</em> computers
</td>
</tr>

